---
title: Garlic Herb Steak with Loaded Potato Skins and Mustardy Snap Peas
description: This recipe has “Sunday dinner” written all over it: our chefs wanted to make something for a special meal worth sharing with family, so they put extra attention into every detail. The sirloin steaks get their own special sauce in the form of a flavorful mix of garlic and herbs with a few capers for garnish. The snap peas, too, are anything but plain—they have a tangy mustard coating. Although the real showstopper might be the stuffed potato skins, which are irresistibly creamy thanks to a nice helping of cheese.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5b5f5130ae08b567c00cc736-9c34effa.jpg
